Senior is a published author, musician

CHRISTINE CLAUS

Senior Melissa Haas was 16
years old when her first book of

poetry was published.

“I’ve always loved to write, and I
just accumulated enough poems to
make a book,” said Haas, who is
known as “Missa” around campus.

“Fairies and Pixiedust” is the
title of Haas’ book that was recently
re—released in its second edition. This
time, proceeds will benefit the
Make-A—Wish Foundation.
LTDbooks offered to buy the rights
of Haas’ “Fairies and Pixiedust” and
donatevthe proceeds to the founda-
tion. -

“My first publisher, Dreams
Unlimited, had a contact with the
Make-A-Wish Foundation and when
they were combined with LTDbo.oks,
it just came together,” Haas said.

“Fairies and Pixiedust” is an
illustrated collection of poetry that
Haas wrote in high school while she
was being home-schooled.

“The book is happy, just plain
old happy,” Haas said. “I think that a
lot of people don’t appreciate what
